Secondly, The Lord ſaies I will come down and talke with thee, and I will take of the Spirit that is one thee, and will put it on them. Now it is cleere in the Scriptures, that Moſes had not onely a ſpirit of Government, but a ſpirit of Prophecy (or preaching of prayer and ſupplication);
                  Exod. 14.15. Deut. 18.15. Act. 7.37. Therefore if God tooke of that ſpirit that was upon Moſes, and gave it to the ſeauenty whereof Eldad & Medad were, then it cannot be reſtrained only to Government, but it muſt extend to all the reſt of

 operations and workes of it, as to prophecie or preach the great matters of Gods law to his people.
